Hard rules from the Constitution (NON-NEGOTIABLE):
- Idempotent webhook handling, DB-level UNIQUE on dedup keys (CP-II / FR-005)
- Test-first; failing test before implementation (CP-III)
- Verify every inbound webhook signature before any business logic (CP-VII)
- Lark `url_verification` handshake handled BEFORE signature verification (CP-VIII)

Layering: 4-layer dependency direction `webhooks → services → clients → models`,
enforced by `import-linter`. Cross-cutting: `app/config.py`, `app/observability.py`.

Forbidden libraries: LangChain, LangGraph, vector DBs, MCP, Redis (until measured
dedup bottleneck), message queues, Celery.
